the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Wilbur, your role in this game is guard.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Joseph\nLast words from Joseph: Thank you all for your support during the game. I wanted to take this opportunity to share my thoughts on who I believe the werewolves are. Based on their behavior and interactions, I think William and Steven are the werewolves. They seemed overly aggressive and defensive during the initial discussions, and their interactions with each other were suspicious. I also want to encourage the players to trust Charlene and Claire, as I believe they are on our side. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves before they can harm the village.\nPlayer Joseph has been eliminated from the game.\nBrian's speech: Thank you, Joseph, for your bravery and your insights. Your words are important, and we should take them into consideration. However, I believe we need more evidence before we can conclusively identify William and Steven as werewolves. Their behavior during the initial discussions was indeed suspicious, but we should not jump to conclusions without more information. I would like to commend Claire and Charlene for their contributions to the village. They have been supportive and helpful, and I believe we should trust them until we have more evidence. Let's work together to gather more information and make an informed decision about who to banish next.\nCharlene's speech: Thank you, Brian, for your thoughtful speech. I agree that we need to gather more evidence before making any accusations. Based on my observations, I have noticed some behavior that seems suspicious. For example, William and Steven have been overly aggressive and defensive during the initial discussions, and their interactions with each other have been quite suspicious. However, I believe we should be cautious about jumping to conclusions without more evidence. Let's work together to gather more information and make an informed decision about who to banish next. I encourage everyone to share their observations and insights, and let's support each other in our efforts to identify and eliminate the werewolves.\nClaire's speech: Thank you, Brian and Charlene, for your thoughtful and cautious speeches. I agree that we need to gather more evidence before making any accusations. Their behavior during the initial discussions was suspicious, but we should not jump to conclusions without more information. I would like to commend Claire and Charlene for their contributions to the village. They have been supportive and helpful, and I believe we should trust them until we have more evidence. Let's work together to gather more information and make an informed decision about who to banish next. We need to be vigilant and careful, but we can do this if we support each other and stay focused on our goal of eliminating the werewolves.\nPhillip's speech: Thank you, Brian, Charlene, and Claire, for your thoughtful and cautious speeches. It's clear that we need to be careful and gather more evidence before making any accusations. I would like to share a piece of information that I believe will be helpful. Last night, I checked Charlene, and I can confirm that she is not a werewolf. This should give us some peace of mind and allow us to focus on other players. I also encourage the Guard to protect someone important tonight, as we 